{
  "texts": [
    "-Venue, which describes why this district court is the correct one to hear this case.",
    "District courts are federal trial courts in the U.S. -Parties, which describes the plaintiffs and the defendants in the case, including why the court has jurisdiction over the defendants and the subject matter in question.",
    "-Facts, which lays out the events and defendant's actions, on which the plaintiff's legal claims are based.",
    "-Legal claims, each of which is one \"Count\" against the defendant.",
    "Each count is a separate section and explains why the facts of the case support each allegation."
  ]
}